# Architecture

## HOOK-ENFORCED (will be blocked)
- Max 300 lines per file. If a file exceeds this, split it into smaller modules.
- kebab-case for ALL folder names. No camelCase or PascalCase directories.
- Infrastructure layers (`ws/`, `infrastructure/`) are READ-ONLY for AI. Do not modify these files without explicit approval.
- Do NOT create new files in `components/ui/` without explicit approval. Compose from existing ShadCN components.

## INSTRUCTION RULES

### Feature-first organization
```
src/
├── features/
│   ├── {feature-name}/
│   │   ├── store/          # Jotai atoms, actions, listeners, handlers, types
│   │   ├── components/     # Feature-specific components
│   │   ├── hooks/          # Feature-specific hooks
│   │   └── types.ts        # Feature types
├── components/
│   └── ui/                 # ShadCN primitives ONLY
├── hooks/                  # Truly global hooks (useIsMobile, etc.)
├── lib/                    # Utilities and adapters
└── ws/ (or infrastructure/)  # Infrastructure layer (READ-ONLY)
```

- Global hooks in `hooks/`, utilities in `lib/`.
- Routing must be modular by page, whether file-based, virtual, or code-based.
- Effect library is encouraged for service composition and error handling.
